 {"id":"git_safety_guard-gmxz","title":"[E10-T4] Implement warning/soft-block/hard-block responses","description":"## Task: Implement warning/soft-block/hard-block responses

### Parent Epic
Epic 10: Graduated Response System (git_safety_guard-yejh)

### What To Do
Create distinct response handlers for each graduation level.

### Implementation Details
1. Response enum:
   ```rust
   pub enum GraduatedResponse {
       Warning {
           message: String,
           occurrence: u32,  // "1st time this session"
       },
       SoftBlock {
           message: String,
           occurrence: u32,
           requires_confirmation: bool,
       },
       HardBlock {
           message: String,
           total_occurrences: u32,
       },
   }
   ```

2. Warning handler (allows command):
   ```rust
   fn handle_warning(command: &str, response: &GraduatedResponse) -> Outcome {
       eprintln!("⚠️  WARNING: {}", command);
       eprintln!("This command is potentially dangerous.");
       eprintln!("(First occurrence this session - command allowed)");
       Outcome::Allow
   }
   ```

3. Soft block handler (requires confirmation):
   ```rust
   fn handle_soft_block(command: &str, response: &GraduatedResponse) -> Outcome {
       eprintln!("🟡 SOFT BLOCK: {}", command);
       eprintln!("You've run this dangerous command {} times this session.", occurrence);
       eprint!("Type 'yes' to proceed, or press Enter to cancel: ");

       let mut input = String::new();
       std::io::stdin().read_line(&mut input)?;

       if input.trim().to_lowercase() == "yes" {
           Outcome::Allow
       } else {
           Outcome::Block
       }
   }
   ```

4. Hard block handler (no override):
   ```rust
   fn handle_hard_block(command: &str, response: &GraduatedResponse) -> Outcome {
       eprintln!("🛑 HARD BLOCK: {}", command);
       eprintln!("This command has been blocked {} times.", total);
       eprintln!("Add to allowlist if this is intentional: dcg allow \"{}\"", command);
       Outcome::Block
   }
   ```

### Output Styling
- WARNING: Yellow/amber color, ⚠️ icon
- SOFT BLOCK: Orange color, 🟡 icon
- HARD BLOCK: Red color, 🛑 icon

### Files to Modify
- src/evaluator.rs (response handling)
- src/output/denial.rs (graduated output)

